    "raw": "Add a --create flag to `todo set` that performs mint first, then applies the usual set fields, and prints the resulting Id. Drop `mint` as a subcommand. Rewrite the todos skill (and any CLI docs/tests) to use `todo set --create ...` instead of the mint-then-set flow.\n\nAcceptance direction:\n- `todo.py set --create [--summary=...] [--body=...] [--ac=...] ...` creates a pre-init record (no git branch), applies the provided fields, prints the 64-hex Id (same stdout contract mint had).\n- Remove `todo.py mint` subcommand; update SKILL.md, help text, and tests accordingly.\n- Preserve set's existing behavior when --create is absent (current-branch or --id target).\n- --create and --id together should be rejected or clearly defined (prefer reject: create always mints a new Id)."
  },
